e [[Brunei|Sultanate of Brunei]]. It was formed in 1974 and maintains approximately 2,000 [[Gurkha|Gurkhas]].<ref name=nationsencyclopedia-Brunei>[http://www.nationsencyclopedia.com/Asia-and-Oceania/Brunei-Darussalam.html Brunei Darussalam], [http://www.nationsencyclopedia.com/index.html Encyclopedia of the Nations]</ref>\n\nUnit members are all [[British Army]] veterans who function primarily as a [[praetorian guard]] to protect the [[Sultan of Brunei|sultan]], the Royal Family, and major oil installations.They also work as a special forces directly under the command of the Sultan as well as alongside Special Forces Regiment and Special Combat Squadron of the [[Royal Brunei Armed Forces]].\n\nIt is subordinate to the Security and Defence Section of the [[Ministry of Home Affairs (Brunei)|Brunei Ministry of Home Affairs]].\n\n==Notes==\n{{loc}}{{reflist}}\n\n==See also==\n* [[Military of Brunei]]\n* [[Gurkha Contingent]]\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.photius.com/countries/nepal/national_security/nepal_national_security_gurkhas_serving_abro~10154.htmlGurkas serving abroad at Photius.com]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20080117160705/http://www.geocities.com/pacific_oob/RBAF.htm RBAF Order of Battle]\n* [http://www.army.mod.uk/gurkhas/27784.aspx Brigade of Gurkhas]\n\n<!--Navigation box--><br />\n{{Asia topic|Military of|title=Militaries of Asia}}\n{{Asia topic|Law enforcement in}}\n\n[[Category:Law enforcement agencies of Brunei]]\n[[Category:Military of Brunei|*]]\n[[Category:Gurkhas]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox government agency\n| name                 = Gurkha Reserve Unit\n| native_name          = \n| native_name_a        = \n| native_name_r        = \n| type                 = Department\n| seal                 = \n| seal_width           = \n| seal_caption         = \n| logo                 = \n| logo_width           = \n| logo_caption         = \n| image                = \n| image_size           = \n| image_caption        = \n| formed               = 1974\n| preceding1           = \n| preceding2           = <!-- up to |preceding6= -->\n| dissolved            = \n| superseding1         = \n| superseding2         = <!-- up to |superseding6= -->\n| jurisdiction         = [[Brunei]]\n| headquarters         = \n| coordinates          = \n| motto                = \n| employees            = \n| budget               = \n| minister1_name       = \n| minister1_pfo        = \n| minister2_name       = \n| minister2_pfo        = <!-- up to |minister8_name= -->\n| deputyminister1_name = \n| deputyminister1_pfo  = \n| deputyminister2_name = \n| deputyminister2_pfo  = <!-- up to |deputyminister8_name= -->\n| chief1_name          = \n| chief1_position      = Commander\n| chief2_name          = \n| chief2_position      = Deputy Commander\n| public_protector     = \n| deputy               = \n| parent_department    = [[Ministry of Home Affairs (Brunei)|Brunei Ministry of Home Affairs]]\n| parent_agency        = \n| child1_agency        = \n| child2_agency        = <!-- up to |child25_agency= -->\n| keydocument1         = <!-- up to |keydocument6= -->\n| website              = \n| agency_id            =\n| map                  = \n| map_size             = \n| map_caption          = \n| footnotes            = \n| embed                = \n}}\nThe '''Gurkha Reserve Unit''' ([[Malay language|Malay]]: ''Unit Simpanan Gurkha'') is a [[Nepal]]ese special elite guard force in the [[Brunei|Sultanate of Brunei]]. It was formed in 1974 and maintains approximately 2,000 [[Gurkha|Gurkhas]].<ref name=nationsencyclopedia-Brunei>[http://www.nationsencyclopedia.com/Asia-and-Oceania/Brunei-Darussalam.html Brunei Darussalam], [http://www.nationsencyclopedia.com/index.html Encyclopedia of the Nations]</ref>\n\nUnit members are all [[British Army]] veterans who function primarily as a [[praetorian guard]] to protect the [[Sultan of Brunei|sultan]], the Royal Family, and major oil installations.They also work as a special forces directly under the command of the Sultan as well as alongside Special Forces Regiment and Special Combat Squadron of the [[Royal Brunei Armed Forces]].\n\nIt is subordinate to the Security and Defence Section of the [[Ministry of Home Affairs (Brunei)|Brunei Ministry of Home Affairs]].\n\n==Notes==\n{{loc}}{{reflist}}\n\n==See also==\n* [[Military of Brunei]]\n* [[Gurkha Contingent]]\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.photius.com/countries/nepal/national_security/nepal_national_security_gurkhas_serving_abro~10154.htmlGurkas serving abroad at Photius.com]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20080117160705/http://www.geocities.com/pacific_oob/RBAF.htm RBAF Order of Battle]\n* [http://www.army.mod.uk/gurkhas/27784.aspx Brigade of Gurkhas]\n\n<!--Navigation box--><br />\n{{Asia topic|Military of|title=Militaries of Asia}}\n{{Asia topic|Law enforcement in}}\n\n[[Category:Law enforcement agencies of Brunei]]\n[[Category:Military of Brunei|*]]\n[[Category:Gurkhas]]\n", "name_user": "Dl2000", "label": "safe", "comment": "repair template damage", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gurkha_Reserve_Unit"}
